OL,6,FAmong the veterans' memories of VE Day
OL,7,Fwere humorous drunken tales `
OL,8,Fincluding a commander in a dinghy and
OL,9,Fa sailor stripping off on a crane `
OL,10,Falongside more poignant stories, such
OL,11,Fas a fatal flight after the war ended.
OL,13,FD-Day pilot John Haddock, 102, from
OL,14,FStourbridge in the West Midlands, who
OL,15,Fwas stationed in Scotland when it was
OL,16,Fannounced the conflict would end,
OL,17,Fremembered the celebrations of his
OL,18,Fsozzled squadron.
