OL,6,FMr Haddock said his commanding officer
OL,7,F` Max Aitken, the son of the wartime
OL,8,Faircraft production minister Lord
OL,9,FBeaverbrook, got into a water dinghy
OL,10,Fand "launched" himself into the
OL,11,Fairfield's static water pool, while
OL,12,Fhis men splashed him.
OL,14,FHe added: "It was all very schoolboy
OL,15,Fbut provided much hilarity at the
OL,16,Ftime."
OL,18,FThree days later, his squadron flew
OL,19,FCrown Prince Olav to Norway after five
OL,20,Fyears in exile, he said.
