OL,6,FThe watercolour illustrations were
OL,7,Fcreated by Martin Impey, known for his
OL,8,Fartwork interpreting one of Wilfred
OL,9,FOwen's war poems, who said he "jumped
OL,10,Fat the chance" to get involved.
OL,12,FHe went on: "It's so important that we
OL,13,Fcommemorate this moment as one of the
OL,14,Flast times as a nation that we can
OL,15,Fshow love, respect, and appreciation
OL,16,Fto a generation who gave so much for
OL,17,Fus all. It was an honour to connect
OL,18,Fwith these heroes and to illustrate
OL,19,Ftheir memories of VE Day."
